  "description": {
    "en": "One of the largest butterflies in the world, with dazzling, iridescent blue wings that flash like a neon sign in the rainforest canopy.",
    "zh": "世界上最大的蝴蝶之一，拥有耀眼、闪烁着虹彩的蓝色翅膀，在雨林树冠层中它就像一块闪烁的霓虹招牌。"
  },
  "encyclopedia": {
    "anatomy": {
      "en": "Their wingspan can reach up to 20 centimeters. The brilliant blue isn't actually a pigment—it's created by the microscopic scales on their wings reflecting light! The underside of their wings is brown with large eyespots for camouflage.",
      "zh": "它们的翼展可达20厘米。那绚烂的蓝色根本不是因为体内有色素——而是由它们翅膀上的微观鳞片反射光线形成的！它们翅膀的底面则是棕色的，并长有用于伪装的巨大眼斑。"
    },
    "ecology_and_behavior": {
      "en": "Blue morphos do not drink flower nectar. Instead, they use sensors on their legs to 'taste' rotting fruit, tree sap, and even fermenting fungi found on the forest floor.",
      "zh": "大蓝闪蝶并不吸食花蜜。相反，它们利用腿部的传感器去「品尝」森林地表上腐烂的水果、树液甚至发酵的真菌。"
    },
    "habitat_and_distribution": {
      "en": "They are native to the tropical forests of Central and South America, particularly widespread throughout the Amazon. They spend most of their time flying rapidly through the understory.",
      "zh": "它们原产于中美洲和南美洲的热带森林，特别是在亚马逊地区分布广泛。它们大部分时间都在森林底层急速飞行。"
    }
  },
